Someone asked what sauce to dip these in... I like an Orange Marmalade Sauce. Sorry for the formatting, I don't know how to force breaks in the lines. Ingredients: 1 teaspoon cornstarch 1 Tablespoon cold water 1/3 cup orange marmalade 1 clove garlic, finely minced 1/8 teaspoon grated ginger 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes 1/4 cup lime juice 1/4 cup soy sauce Preparation: Whisk together cornstarch and cold water. Set aside. Place orange marmalade, garlic, ginger, pepper flakes, lime juice, and soy sauce in a small heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Add cornstarch and simmer, stirring, until sauce is thickened. Remove from heat.

