Rating: 3
Once you resign yourself to the time it takes to produce (almost four hours), the flavours are definitely worth it. Follow the suggestions of previous reviewers and let it marinate overnight, tossing occasionally - a more efficient use of your time. I also strained the fat out of the marinade after the hour in the oven and tossed it (the fat, that is), reheating the marinade on the stove and thickening it with a little Wondra flour in cold water. It made a perfect dip for the winglets. Be aware that if you use a deep fryer, this will be the last use you make of that particular batch of oil, because of the cornstarch residue - it will lower the temperature of the oil and burn more easily on subsequent batches. I got two or three recipes' worth of these delicious wings from my oil before I replaced it.

