I was getting tired of the same ol' Buffalo chicken wings, so I thought this recipe would be a nice change; it was a winning change. I added some sesame chili oil to the marinade for added kick. I'm not partial to the wing drummettes one finds in the supermarket as they tend to be pretty slim pickins'. Instead I bought some whole wings and cut them in half, discarding the tip. Takes a little more time, but the bird is infintely better this way. Salt and Pepper for dipping? I don't get it. Reserve the marinade, reheat, strain and pour over.

Rating: 4
Wow! Very good - these were a big hit. I added 1/4 cup each soy sauce and sherry to the marinade (otherwise it would have been very dry), and marinated the wings for almost 8 hours in the fridge - just more convenient to do it while I was at work. They came out superb. I have never used corn starch to dredge chicken before, but was very pleased with the results (and I skipped serving the wings with the bowl of salt and pepper(?)). Will definitely make these again.

